The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Gangster held after shootout
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      Gangster held after shootout
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	Bhubaneswar, Jan. 1: Sushil Dhalsamant, a wanted gangster in Cuttack, was arrested near the Airfield area here last night.        
	Three policemen and a criminal were injured in the fierce gun-battle that ended in the arrest. The injured criminal, with bullet injuries on his right knee, was rushed to the Capital Hospital and then SCB Medical College and Hospital in Cuttack.        
	Three policemen, including an inspector, received minor injuries..        
	The special squad of the city police based on a tip-off intercepted Sushil in the Aerodrome. When asked to stop, the gangster fired at the police. The accused first fired at a police vehicle. Our men immediately retaliated. In the ensuing battle, Sushil was injured, said DCP Himanshu Lal.         
	More than six cases, including three of murder, are pending against Sushil in Cuttack police stations.         
	The accused was also involved in the double murder case in Chauliaganj police station, police sources said.                                                                                                                                                          
